sentences: Jim Nesbitt (December 1, 1931 – November 29, 2007) was an American country music singer.
He had his first hit with "Please Mr. Kennedy" in 1961.
His biggest hit, "Lookin' for More in '64", got to number 7.
It stayed on the Cash Box charts for 13 weeks.
He released his last album, Phone Call From The Devil, in 1975 on Scorpion Records.
